        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 2:48AM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 248 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from over Tybee Island to 12 miles southeast
of Forest Beach, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hilton Head Island, Forest Beach, Lawton, Calibogue Cay, Folly
Field, Hilton Head Airport, Wilton Graves Bridge, Caril Bowers
Bridge, Bluffton and Parris Island.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
